{@comment define macros that help the use of the built-in ruby macros}

{@comment

You can use this macro to declare the name of the ruby shell in case there are multiple shells used in the
Jamal file. One possibility is to [@define rubyShell= name ]

The other one is to use this macro and say [shell=name]

}
{@define shell(x)={@define rubyShell=x}}